VOLDEMORT Schema Comparison Report

Compare two VistA versions, RPMS ('Other') against GOLD ('Baseline'). This report shows which files and fields are shared and which are exclusive to one or other VistA. For each file, the report also gives a count of its entries as reported by its FileMan. The most relevant information is highlighted in grey.

Warning: This report was generated by VDM Version .3. This is development software.

Jump to: Counts | In Both | RPMS Only | GOLD Only

Schema Counts

Overall
9028 files, 2872 in both
GOLD ("Baseline")
5622 files, 2448 tops, 3174 multiples, 2750 unique, 1223 populated (50.0%)
56482 fields, 25223 in shared files, 1654 unique
RPMS ("Other")
6278 files, 2618 tops, 3660 multiples, 3406 unique (54.2%), 1223 populated (46.7%)
235122 fields, 26207 in shared files, 969 unique, 378 repurposed, 1347 custom (5.1%)

Differences between Files in Both

Files common to both VistAs that have schema as opposed to content differences. Fields unique to GOLD ("missing fields") means RPMS has fallen behind and is missing some builds present in GOLD. Fields unique to RPMS ("custom fields") means it has added custom entries not found in GOLD. Entries labeled "field name mismatch" show fields with different names in each VistA. Some mismatches are superficial name variations but many represent the use of the same field for different purposes by each system. Note that this list does not highlight differences in Lab files - local sites customize these extensively. There needs to be a separate 'lab differences' report.

Files only in RPMS

3406 files are unique to RPMS. Along with custom fields added to common files, these indicate the extent of custom functionality in this VistA. Descriptions should help distinguish between files once released centrally by the VA - 'Property of the US Government ...' - and files local to the VistA being compared.
